WEBVTT

00:00:00.171 --> 00:00:07.374
Why do highly competent managers consistently fail when attempting to scale their decision-making across boundaryless global enterprises?

00:00:08.315 --> 00:00:14.337
The failure stems from relying on linear managerial tactics in nonlinear, culturally complex systems.

00:00:15.298 --> 00:00:19.900
Success requires engineering an environment for active, self-built understanding.

00:00:20.780 --> 00:00:22.541
This is not a theoretical exercise.

00:00:23.446 --> 00:00:30.754
Mastering the causal mechanisms of global leadership is the direct path to professional mastery and self actualization.
